During the first snow of the year 3 year-old Nate Denton wanders away from his father's truck 
and disappears. The fevered search for him ends with the devastating discover of his tiny, 
frozen body. Nate's death throws the small foothills community of Angel's Crest into disarray. 
The inhabitants confront what Nate's death means to them and in the face of that struggle they 
deal with their own concepts of right and wrong.
